    <note>Li(2) Zhoushi [1007]  His great great grandfather, Feng [3496], was a Jingzhao, Changan resident who served as a Tang dynasty military official. His great grandfather, Chou [3475], was a Later Liang prefect who fled the late Tang rebellions to live in Sichuan. According to the Sichuan TZ, his father, Jianzhong [3483], was a 983 Chengdu, Chengdu xian jinshi, who subsequently lived in Henan, Luoyang xian. Zhoumin's [3486] and Zhoudao's [3488] brother. Zhoushi and Zhoudao, are listed as Chengdu jinshi in 988. XCB, 98.9a; SS, 441.16b; Sichuan TZ, 122.7a, 8a. CBD, 2, 997.</note>
